image.altText: Sam Kerr

items.synopsis: The Matildas are down 2-0 in their World Cup third-place playoff clash with Sweden, with Sam Kerr appearing to suffer a leg injury. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: Battered and bruised Matildas trail 2-0 in third-place playoff with Sweden

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: She was on the ground for an age as play went on around her, but the referee couldn't find a spot to pause it. It's Kerr's right calf (not her previously injured one, for the record) and it was a contact injury, which is good news. She copped a knee in the lower leg, so that's better than it just going ping while she was running. Kerr limps back on to thunderous applause. I don't know how much of an impact she'll be able to have with two crocked calves, but she wants to go out on her shield.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 75' Sam Kerr is down!

Kerr limps back on to thunderous applause. I don't know how much of an impact she'll be able to have with two crocked calves, but she wants to go out on her shield.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Again it's the speed of Blackstenius doing the damage. She gets in behind Clare Hunt, and while Hunt recovers well to make a play, she can't stop the Swedish striker from laying a ball back on for captain Kosovare Asllani, who drills a shot just inside the right post.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SWEDEN SCORES AGAIN!! It's 2-0 now

children.content: Again it's the speed of Blackstenius doing the damage. She gets in behind Clare Hunt, and while Hunt recovers well to make a play, she can't stop the Swedish striker from laying a ball back on for captain Kosovare Asllani, who drills a shot just inside the right post.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: No half-time substitutes for either side. Australia's play off the kick-off, which they've tried a few times, is basically sending Kyra Cooney-Cross on a recon mission forward, but she stacks and hands possession over. It gives Sweden the first chance of the half, but Rolfo slices her shot well wide and into the crowd.

It gives Sweden the first chance of the half, but Rolfo slices her shot well wide and into the crowd.
